  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
        <div xml:id="KT81-kilavi">
          <p type="edition">tōḻiyiṟ kūṭṭaṅ kūṭip piriyun talaimakaṟkut tōḻi colliyatu.</p>
          <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">Uttered by the confidante to HIM who separated after having begged for the help of the confidante.</p>
          </div>



        <div xml:id="KT81">
            <lg type="edition">
<l>                ivaḷē</l>
<l>                niṉcoṟ koṇṭa veṉcoṟ ṟēṟip</l>
<l>                pacunaṉai ñāḻaṟ palciṉai yoruciṟaip</l>
<l>                putunala ṉiḻanta pulampumā ruṭaiya</l>
<l>                ḷutukkāṇ ṭeyya vuḷḷal vēṇṭu</l>
<l>                nilavu miruḷum pōlap pulavuttiraik</l>
<l>                kaṭaluṅ kāṉalun tōṉṟu</l>
<l>                maṭaṟāḻ peṇṇaiyeñ ciṟunal lūrē.</l>
             </lg>
            <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
          <l>This one, after</l>
          <l rend="indent">my words that had taken up your words became clear [to her],<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">koṇṭa</term>: "my words that had taken [up] your words [and transmitted them to her]".</note></l>
            
          <l rend="indent">as<note place="foot">Actually, since the temporal sequence is clear, the <term xml:lang="ta">peyareccam iḻanta</term> is hard to defend, that is, clearly preferable is the variant <term xml:lang="ta">iḻantu</term>, absolutive. Cām. gives a variant of that type, but this is not confirmed anywhere else and might represent a normalisation.</note> [her] innocence is lost</l>
          <l rend="indent">on one side of the many-branched Ñāḻal<note place="foot">Here word order <term xml:lang="ta">ñāḻal palciṉai</term> might be explained as an inversion for the sake of euphony.</note> with green buds,</l>
          <l rend="indent3">is possessed by loneliness</l>
          <l>– just<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">teyya</term> is satisfactorily explained as a particle of admonition.</note> look there!</l>
          <l>Our good little village<note place="foot">Or, perhaps equally convincing, a circular connection: "This one ... in our small good village ...", inserting the line of the main sentence consisting in imperative + comment: "just look there: Remembering is necessary."</note>, [among] Palmyra trees with hanging stems,</l>
          <l rend="indent2">must be thought of,</l>
          <l rend="indent">where seashore grove and sea with waves reeking of fish</l>
          <l rend="indent">appear like darkness and moonlight.</l>
          <lg type="alternate" resp="#TVG" sameAs="1b">
            <l>This one, believing my words [she] had taken for your words ...</l>
          </lg>
            </lg>
        </div>
